personality_type_1.name: Analyzer
personality_type_1.description: 'Analyzers'...are inquisitive.  They delve, study and look deeply for information.  They have a keen eye and an experimental nature.  Analyzers use these capacities to figure out problems and search for the facts, often in a laboratory environment.  They excel at going beyond the surface toward uncovering information and discovery.
personality_type_1.keywords: investigating, solving, researching, delving, examining, discovering, introversion

personality_type_2.name: Mentor
personality_type_2.description: 'Mentors'...are people-oriented.  They have great communication skills and are most fulfilled when assisting or working directly with others to improve a personal or societal situation. Mentors are patient and compassionate and work best in a group or on a team with a common goal. Mentors excel at working with others to help them learn and grow.
personality_type_2.keywords: helping, assisting, teaching, caring, interacting, improving (situations/lives), working as a team, having a greater goal

personality_blend.name: Analyzer/Mentor
personality_blend.description: You are a natural helper and get fulfillment from taking part in others' lives in a meaningful way.  You always look beyond the surface and are thoughtful and mindful in your work and your interactions with others. In a group of people, you often find yourself watching out for everyone in the group, making sure they are having a good time.  You have many intellectual interests and a natural curiosity about the world.  Your friends appreciate your ideas and deep thinking.  Happy in a group of people, you also enjoy time with a few close friends spent in meaningful and thought-provoking discussion.

details.title: Conflict
details.body: You pride yourself in getting along with all types of people and are fortunate in that you work well with everyone.  You may find, however, that you have to adjust your style for your Action-Taker colleagues.  You prefer to work on teams with regular meetings and communication, while Action-Takers like to work on solitary projects.  You also put careful thought and consideration into everything you do.  Your Action-Taker and Inventor colleagues tend to jump right into projects which may feel risky to you.

details.title: Complement
details.body: You like to work with other Mentors who share your passion for teamwork and helping others. Communication is important to you, and you respect that ability in others.  You also like to work with other Analyzers whose shared cerebral interests find you having many things in common.  You also appreciate your Planner colleagues who are methodical in their approach to work. You admire and rely on their organized approach to work and life.

environments.name: Allows for independent study and peer collaboration

personality_type.name: Action-Taker
personality_type.description: 'Action-Takers'...are hands-on doers.  They use manual and physical skills, working with technology or machinery to complete tasks.  Often there is an athletic aspect to their work.  They are handy, practical, systematic, applied, and 'down-to-earth.'  They are drawn to jobs that involve a specific skill-set and a concrete task.  They excel at solitary, goal-oriented work and 'getting the job done.'
personality_type.keywords: goal-setting, accomplishing, tinkering, doing, fixing, using tools/machines, hands-on, physical, concrete tasks

personality_type.name: Naturalist
personality_type.description: 'Naturalists'...are attached to the natural world, frequently working with plants and animals in their  environment.  Often nature lovers, they like to experience the world outdoors.  They are committed to preserving and protecting the planet and its natural resources. Serene, earthy, efficient and solid, they excel at working as one with the natural environment.
personality_type.keywords: sustaining, preserving, conserving, maintaining, improving, working outdoors, communing with the natural world

personality_type.name: Planner
personality_type.description: 'Planners'...are the detail people.  They are methodical, precise, and detail-oriented.  Planners create systems to follow, and enjoy working with data, detail, words and numbers.  Great at manipulating data, they love procedure and routine.  Often found in office settings, they excel at completing detailed work in an organized manner.
personality_type.keywords: planning, organizing, keeping order, perfecting, filing, working with numbers

personality_type.name: Visionary
personality_type.description: 'Visionaries'...are pioneers.  They are great convincers and like to work with others in a 'take charge' capacity.  They love to take risks, make changes and set trends.  They tend to be   ambitious and energetic.  Visionaries are often in positions of prominence in business and the public eye and excel at taking charge and gaining the confidence of others.
personality_type.keywords: leading, managing, selling, trend-setting, persuading, competing, moving forward, extroversion

personality_type.name: Inventor
personality_type.description: 'Inventors'...are creative.  They take a contemporary, 'out of the box' approach to work and life. Inventors use themselves and other medium, often various forms of the arts, to communicate and interact with the world.  Inventors excel when they are 'lost' in their work, completely engrossed in a project.
personality_type.keywords: creating, expressing, innovating, inventing, entertaining, expanding art
